  "texts": [
    "This is discussed in more depth in the introductory Section 1, Subsection 1.2.",
    "Here we only reitarate, that the dualisation methods employed by Bourgain and Brezis [10] and McMullen [33] together with the noninequality of Ornstein [35] could likely be adjusted to yield similar results for the general exterior derivative operator.",
    "Given that this is not available in the literature and that these results can be immediately obtained from our main non-regularity result, we provide here the full statement with rigorous proof.",
    "We denote by L ∞ cl ([0, 1] d, k R d) the subspace of distributionally closed L ∞ differential kforms, i.e.",
    "those forms ω for which dω = 0 distributionally."
  ]
